Formal Grammar for tpt-telos (v0.2.0)
=======================================

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Language Feature Matrix
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SUPPORTED (verifier + all backends):
  Arithmetic operators    +  -  *  /  (unary -)
  Comparison operators    ==  !=  <  <=  >  >=
  Logical conjunction     &&  (in requires/ensures)
  Logical disjunction     ||  (via DNF normalization)
  Post-conditions         ensures e        (provable from requires + mutations)
  Pre-conditions          requires e       (assumed true in pre-state)
  Pre-state reference     old(expr)        (e.g. old(w.balance))
  Mutation block          mutate state { target (= | += | -=) expr; }
  Field paths             e.g. wallet.balance, s.pressure
  Invariant types         invariant T { constraint }  (checked at entry + post-mutate)
  Refinement type         PositiveInt      (built-in; treated as Int with balance >= 0 premise)
  Module attributes       @boundary(...)   (routing), @state(...)  (storage class, parsed only)
  Function attributes     @eject           (compile as trusted opaque + contract guard)
  Routing flags           cpu_bound  zero_allocation  crypto  real_time      → Rust
                          network_io  high_concurrency  distributed  high_latency → Go
                          ml_training  python  jax                            → Python
  Nonlinear contracts     x * y < K        (verified via interval bounding when bounds present;
                                            marked [interval-bounded] in output)
  Float types             Float32/Float64  (IEEE 754 interval arithmetic in IR)
  Bounded quantifiers     forall i in lo..hi { body }  (unrolled to conjunctions)
  Aggregate expressions   sum/count over bounded ranges
  Modular verification    Call/MethodCall resolved via callee ensures
  Array/slice contracts   Constant-index access in contracts

NEW IN v0.2.0 (koinon feature set):
  Return types            func f(x: T) -> Result<T, E>  (generic return types)
  Let bindings            let x [: Type] = expr;
  Function calls          func_name(args) in expressions
  Method calls            receiver.method(args)
  Quantified invariants   forall x: Type in lo..hi { body }  (bounded range unrolling)
  Aggregate expressions   sum/count over bounded ranges
  Mutable parameters      mut sender: Account
  Control flow            if expr { stmts } [else { stmts }]
                          if expr { expr } else { expr }  (expression form)
                          match expr { pattern => expr, ... }
  Struct definitions      struct Name { field: Type, ... }
  Enum definitions        enum Name { Variant { field: Type }, Variant2, ... }
  Error propagation       expr?
  Patterns                literal | var | Constructor(fields...) | _
  Range expressions       lo..hi  (exclusive upper bound, for forall/aggregate domains)
  Modular verification    Call/MethodCall resolved via callee ensures substitution
  Constant-index arrays   arr[constant] in contracts

PARTIAL / LIMITED:
  Logical disjunction     ||  parsed; DNF normalization for requires (splits into sub-problems);
                                DNF for ensures with or_group tracking (at least one branch must hold)
  @state(...) semantics   parsed and forwarded to router; storage-class behavior enforced
                                (persistent → serde/JSON tags; ephemeral → stack-only)
  Floating-point types    Float32/Float64 parsed and codegen'd to f32/f64 (Rust) and
                                float32/float64 (Go); IR tracks as integer constraints
  Quantifier verification forall is parsed and codegen'd to runtime checks; no formal verification
  Modular verification    Call/MethodCall resolved via callee ensures substitution
  Array/slice contracts   Constant-index access (arr[0]) in contracts; symbolic indices rejected

UNSUPPORTED (parse error or silent drop):
  Strings / booleans      no string or bool literal types
  Symbolic array indices  non-constant index in contracts rejected
  Array length invariants  arrays parsed ([T; N]) but no IR length/index constraint extraction
  Cross-module refs       invariant types resolve across modules (global invariant lookup works)
                                but no explicit cross-module type reference syntax

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Notation: EBNF. `{ ... }*` zero-or-more, `{ ... }+` one-or-more,
`[ ... ]` optional, `( ... )` grouping. `//` introduces a comment.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Program
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

program        ::= module*

module         ::= attribute* "module" IDENT "{" item* "}"

attribute      ::= "@" IDENT [ "(" arglist? ")" ]

arglist        ::= arg ( "," arg )*

arg            ::= IDENT                      // flag, e.g. cpu_bound
                 | IDENT "=" literal          // key/value, e.g. replication_factor = 3

literal        ::= INT | IDENT

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Items
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

item           ::= invariant
                 | func
                 | struct_def
                 | enum_def

invariant      ::= "invariant" IDENT "{"
                       constraint ( ";" constraint )* ";"?
                   "}"

func           ::= "func" IDENT "(" params? ")" [ "->" type ]
                       clause*
                       block | ";"

struct_def     ::= "struct" IDENT "{"
                       field_def ( "," field_def )* ","?
                   "}"

enum_def       ::= "enum" IDENT "{"
                       variant_def ( "," variant_def )* ","?
                   "}"

variant_def    ::= IDENT [ "{" field_def ( "," field_def )* ","? "}" ]

field_def      ::= IDENT ":" type

params         ::= param ( "," param )*

param          ::= [ "mut" ] IDENT ":" type

clause         ::= "requires" constraint
                 | "ensures"  constraint

block          ::= "{" stmt* "}"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Statements
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

stmt           ::= "mutate" "state" "{" assign* "}"
                 | "let" IDENT [ ":" type ] "=" expr ";"
                 | if_stmt
                 | "match" expr "{" match_arm_stmt* "}"
                 | "return" [ expr ] ";"
                 | assign
                 | expr "=" expr ";"
                 | expr "+=" expr ";"
                 | expr "-=" expr ";"
                 | expr ";"               // expression statement

if_stmt        ::= "if" expr "{" stmt* "}" [ "else" "{" stmt* "}" ]

match_arm_stmt ::= pattern "=>" "{" stmt* "}"
                 | pattern "=>" stmt

assign         ::= target ( "=" | "+=" | "-=" ) expr ";"

target         ::= expr        // must resolve to a field path, e.g. from.balance

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Patterns
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

pattern        ::= INT
                 | "-" INT
                 | IDENT [ "(" pattern ( "," pattern )* ")" ]
                 | "_"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Types
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

type           ::= IDENT                            // Named type
                 | IDENT "<" type ( "," type )* ">"  // Generic type (e.g. Result<T, E>)
                 | "(" type ( "," type )+ ")"        // Tuple type

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Expressions
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

constraint     ::= expr                // a boolean expression (see below)

expr           ::= orExpr

orExpr         ::= andExpr ( "||" andExpr )*

andExpr        ::= cmpExpr ( "&&" cmpExpr )*

cmpExpr        ::= addExpr [ cmpOp addExpr ]      // single comparison

cmpOp          ::= "==" | "!=" | "<" | "<=" | ">" | ">="

addExpr        ::= mulExpr ( ( "+" | "-" ) mulExpr )*

mulExpr        ::= postfix ( ( "*" | "/" ) postfix )*

postfix        ::= primary
                 | postfix "(" arglist? ")"        // function / method call
                 | postfix "." IDENT               // field access / method
                 | postfix "[" expr "]"            // index
                 | postfix "?"                     // try / error propagation

primary        ::= INT
                 | "old" "(" expr ")"
                 | IDENT [ "." IDENT ]             // var or field path
                 | "(" expr ")"
                 | if_expr
                 | match_expr
                 | "forall" IDENT ":" type [ "in" expr ] "{" expr "}"
                 | aggregate_call
                 | "Ok" "(" expr ")"
                 | "Err" "(" expr ")"

if_expr        ::= "if" expr "{" expr "}" "else" "{" expr "}"

match_expr     ::= "match" expr "{"
                       ( pattern "=>" expr ","? )*
                   "}"

aggregate_call ::= ( "sum" | "min" | "max" | "count" ) "(" arglist? ")"

arglist        ::= expr ( "," expr )*

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Lexical rules
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

IDENT          ::= ( ASCII_LETTER | "_" ) ( ASCII_ALNUM | "_" )*
INT            ::= [ "-" ] DIGIT+               // (lexer emits separate '-' token)
COMMENT        ::= "//" ... end-of-line
WS             ::= " " | "\t" | "\n" | "\r"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Semantics (summary)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* `@boundary(...)` and `@state(...)` are architectural metadata consumed by the
  context router (Phase 2+). They are parsed but not verified in Phase 1.

* `invariant T { c }` declares that constraint `c` must hold for every value of
  type `T` -- at function entry (pre-state) and after every mutation (post-state).

* `requires e` are pre-conditions: assumed true in the pre-state.
* `ensures  e` are post-conditions: must be provable in the post-state given the
  `requires` clauses and the `mutate state` assignments.

* `old(e)` refers to the value of `e` in the pre-state.

* `func f(x: T) -> Result<T, E>` declares a function with a generic return type.
  The `?` operator desugars to match/return for error propagation.

* `let x = e;` introduces a local binding; in IR this becomes `x == e`.

* `func_name(args)` in an expression context calls a function. When used in
  specifications, the call is substituted with the function's postconditions.

* `forall x: T { body }` is a universal quantifier. Currently codegen'd to
  runtime assertion loops; no formal verification.

* `sum(xs)`, `min(a, b)`, `max(a, b)`, `count(xs)` are aggregate expressions.

* `mut param: T` marks a parameter as mutable (passed by reference).

* `struct Name { field: Type }` and `enum Name { Variant { ... } }` declare
  named types. Inference also discovers types from field accesses.

* `match expr { pattern => expr }` performs pattern matching. Exhaustiveness
  is not enforced by the parser (a `_` wildcard is recommended).

* No implicit type coercion and no hidden allocation: every operation is named.
